details.name: Arkitect Structures Remastered
details.summary: A cross-platform remake of my Ark Survival Evolved structure mod, Arkitect Structures: Core.

screenshots.title: Made by Gimilkhad
screenshots.description: Three roof angles including Convex and Concave curved options. Also pictured: Roof Rakes & Roof Caps, Half Timber variants for wood & stone walls, slate variants for stone roofs, wood pillar variants, curved pillars, custom adjustable glass, & more.

screenshots.title: Tropical Stilt House by Etholdir
screenshots.description: Tropical Stilt House made by Etholdir. Here you can see a variety of custom ASR thatch parts and styles including bamboo wall variants, steep thatch roofs, and thatch roof "rakes" aka roof side overhangs.

screenshots.title: Made by Gimilkhad
screenshots.description: ASR adds a variety of new visual variants to the Thatch tier, as well as new parts. Here you can see the thatch staircase, rails, half rails, bamboo and woven variants for some of the ceilings and walls, and bamboo roofs.

screenshots.title: House of Etholdir
screenshots.description: "To Rivendell, Master Gamgee. To the House of Etholdir." Etho creates an amazing house utilizing some of the ASR curved roofs and ornate variants on the ASR glass parts. Also in use: JVH Landscape and Klinger's Additional Rustic Structures.

screenshots.title: Modern Beach House by Bubu
screenshots.description: Bubu has mixed and matched appearances from the ASR thatch, wood, stone, and adobe tiers to create this amazing modern beach house. Decorations are a mix of Klinger Additional Rustic Building, Bob's Tall Tales, and Summer Bash skins.

screenshots.title: Federation Cruiser, Halzaroka-class
screenshots.description: The Halzaroka-class Federation Cruiser uses ASR AntiGrav foundations, curved roofs, and the Cyber variant of ASR Tek Pillars. Made by Halzaroka.

screenshots.title: Hobbit Hole by Etholdir
screenshots.description: "In a hole in the ground, there lived a hobbit." Etholdir makes use of ASR Convex Thatch roofs and curved pillars here, as well as JVH landscaping, Western Decor, and Arcadian Custom Cosmetics to make a nice cozy home in the Shire

screenshots.title: Orbital Base by Clappo
screenshots.description: Clappo uses the ASR AntiGrav foundations, which you can see sprinkled along the undersides of his base, to create an unassailable home in the sky.

screenshots.title: Fort Mobster
screenshots.description: Fort Mobster makes use of ASR's multiple roof angles, sloped pillars, and palisade wall variants to defend against the wilds. Made by Mobster

screenshots.title: Rings of Nessa by IAmNessa
screenshots.description: Rings of Nessa by IAmNessa. A magnificent floating base in the sky, it makes use of the ASR AntiGrav foundations to do it more "legitimately" (without using special ini settings). Totally worth the exorbitant element cost.

screenshots.title: Mountain Cottage by Mobster
screenshots.description: Who wouldn't want to move to the mountains and live in this cottage Mobster built? Scute shingle roofing and half-timber frame protects against the elements.

screenshots.title: Skylight by Pickles
screenshots.description: Pickles makes use of one of ASR's most beloved features, the glass. As you can see in his skylight here there are many styles to choose from including various stained glass patterns.

screenshots.title: Watchtower by Mobster
screenshots.description: When I first saw this build I didn't even think it was ASR. What Mobster did here with his watchtower using the sloped pillars was really impressive in my humble opinion.

screenshots.title: Haunted House by Bubu
screenshots.description: Haunted House by Bubu. Or should I say Boo! Boo! (Sorry. I'll see myself out). Mix of ASR and Amissa Structures

screenshots.title: F117 Stealth Quetzal by Jesse F.
screenshots.description: The F117 Stealth Quetzal. Made by Jesse F.

screenshots.title: Cyber Boat by Kethra
screenshots.description: Cyber Boat by Kethra. Uses cyber variant of the ASR Tek Pillars

screenshots.title: Tower of Sarge
screenshots.description: Tower of Sarge. Sarge used advanced building techniques to create this extra-round design

screenshots.title: Casino by Unknown
screenshots.description: Casino by Unknown. If you know who made this please message me so I can give them credit. Other mods used: I think it's Neon Structures. Not sure about the fences. If someone knows please tell me. I'm guessing it's JVH Landscape used for the trees.

screenshots.title: Homestead by RedMustang
screenshots.description: Homestead by RedMustang. Scute Shingles visual variant available for Wood tier roofs. Also pictured: Palisade variant for wood wall, roof cresting variants for the flat wood pillars, and "Eave" roof parts aka bottom roof overhangs.

screenshots.title: Made by Gimilkhad
screenshots.description: Dedicated Glass tiers exist for Wood, Stone, Adobe, Metal, and Tek tiers. Metal tier glass was used in this picture. All ASR glass parts provide greenhouse effect.
